==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|vermeil||vermilion|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|vermiculus||little worm|lang=la}}, the coccus Indicus, from {{term|vermis||worm|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/vɜː(ɹ)ˈmɪl.jən/}}, {{SAMPA|/v3:(r)"mIl.j@n/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪljən}}

===Alternative spellings===
* [[vermillion]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[vivid]] [[red]] [[synthetic]] [[pigment]] made of [[mercury sulfide]].
# {{colour}} A vivid red or slightly [[orange]] [[colour]].
#: {{colour panel|E34234}}
# A type of red dye worn in the parting of the hair by married Hindu women.

